Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Kuwait. The Kuwaiti authorities have introduced measures to limit the spread of the virus.
Entry and borders
The Kuwait Government are no longer allowing non-Kuwaitis to enter Kuwait. Non-Kuwaitis arriving on flights to Kuwait will be required to board the next plane out of Kuwait, until further notice.
Land borders with Iraq and Saudi Arabia have closed, and other countries may monitor travellers from Kuwait.
For information on how to return to the UK from Kuwait, see Return to the UK.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of respiratory diseases, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
You can find more information about cases in Kuwait on the TravelHealthPro country page.
